track_notes: From NW-013 take NW ridge to col and then up to summit of Pen yr Helgi Du. From this summit there is a steep and narrow descent to the next col SH SH 696 630. This is quite simple, but needs care. Cross col to reach a small rock step SH 692 634. Climb this fairly easily to reach the top of Craig Yr Isfa. Follow path easily to summit.  To return head south down to ridge to Carnedd Dafydd and turn west at SH 677 631.  Traverse across slope (no path) until you can drop into Cwm Lloer.  Cross river usually easily at SH 665 618. Be careful if water levels are high. Pick up path south to return to road.

Parking is two pounds (July 2017) at the Gwern Gof Isaf campsite on the A5. Tarmac Welsh Water road (locked gate) up to reservoir then path to Bwlch. Limited amount of scrambling to both summits but quite straightforward if care is taken.

Total time (including ops): 6hr 15m. Maximum difficulty: Swiss Alpine Club Grade T3 / Grade 1 Scramble. Uncurated GPX which may contain navigation errors, detours and hazards.
